<text xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="Fluid_Reading_Text"><body><div change="#StB" n="17" type="r"><sp who="#V."><p><pb facs="#f018"/><milestone facs="#f018_z000" n="17" unit="folio_number"/><lb/>no more a realist than Holbein <milestone facs="#StCa" unit="enclosure"/><add change="#StBb" facs="#Wilde" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline" rend="pencil_enclosure">was</add>.<note rend="small">55</note> He<lb/> created life, he did not copy it. I <lb/>admit, however, that he set far too<lb/> high a value on modernity of form,<lb/> and that <del change="#StC" facs="#f018_z011" hand="#comp">as a consequence</del><add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z011" hand="#comp" place="nc">, consequently,</add> there is<lb/> <del change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z008" hand="#Wilde" rend="single-stroke">nothing </del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z004" hand="#Wilde" place="inspace">no book</add> of his that<add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z012" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> as an<lb/> artistic masterpiece<add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z013" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> can rank with<lb/> <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del><hi change="#StC" facs="#f018_z003" hand="#comp" rend="underline">Salammb√¥</hi><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del> or <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del><hi change="#StC" facs="#f018_z004" hand="#comp" rend="underline">Esmond</hi>,<del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del> or <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del><hi change="#StC" facs="#f018_z005" hand="#comp" rend="underline">The</hi><lb/><hi change="#StC" facs="#f018_z005" hand="#comp" rend="underline"> Cloister and the Hearth</hi><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del>, or the <del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del><hi change="#StB" facs="#f018_z006 #f018_z007" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">Vicomte</hi><lb/><hi change="#StB" facs="#f018_z006 #f018_z007" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline"> de Bragelonne</hi><del change="#StC" hand="#comp">'</del>.<note rend="small">56</note><lb/><note facs="#f018_z014" rend="small">Typesetters Signature: Hirschfield</note></p>
				</sp>
				<sp who="#C.">
					<p><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">C</hi><del change="#StC" facs="#f018_z001" hand="#comp" rend="pencil"><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">yril</hi></del><add change="#StD" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions"><hi rend="italic">yril</hi></add><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">.</hi><lb/>Do you object to modernity of<lb/> form<add change="#StD" facs="#f018_z016" place="intentions">,</add> then<del change="#StD" facs="#f018_z015">?</del><add change="#StD" facs="#f018_z015" place="intentions"><del change="#StE" facs="#f018_z015">!</del></add><add change="#StE" facs="#f018_z015" place="intentions_1894">?</add> <lb/></p>
				</sp>
				<sp who="#V.">
					<p><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">V</hi><del change="#StC" facs="#f018_z002" hand="#comp" rend="pencil"><hi change="#StB" hand="#Wilde" rend="underline">ivian</hi></del><add change="#StD" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions"><hi rend="italic">ivian</hi></add>. <lb/>Yes. It is a huge price to pay<lb/> for a very poor result. Pure <lb/>modernity of form is always <add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z017" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline" rend="caret">somewhat </add><milestone facs="#f018_z017" unit="caret"/>vulgarising.<lb/> It cannot help being so. The public<lb/> imagine that<add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z018" hand="#comp" place="nc">, </add>because they are interested<lb/> in their immediate surroundings<add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z019" hand="#comp" place="nc">,</add> <add change="#StD" facs="#f018_z020" hand="#Wilde" place="intentions">A</add><add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z020" hand="#comp" place="nc"><del change="#StD" facs="#f018_z020">a</del></add><del change="#StC" facs="#f018_z020" hand="#comp">A</del>rt<lb/> should be interested in them also, and<lb/> should take them as her subject<add change="#StC" facs="#f018_z021" hand="#comp" place="nc">-</add><lb/>matter. But the mere fact that they<lb/> are interested in these things makes<lb/> them unsuitable subjects for <add change="#StD" facs="#f018_z022" place="intentions">A</add><del change="#StD" facs="#f018_z022">a</del>rt. The<lb/> only beautiful things, as <del change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z023" hand="#Wilde" rend="multi-stroke">Schopenahuer </del><add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z024" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret">somebody</add><note rend="small">57</note><add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z024" hand="#Wilde" place="above" rend="no_caret"><lb/></add>once said, are the things that do not <lb/>concern us. As long as a thing is <lb/>useful <add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z025" hand="#Wilde" place="above inline" rend="caret">or necessary</add><milestone facs="#f018_z025" unit="caret"/> to us, or affects us in any <lb/>way, either for pain <add change="#StBa" facs="#f018_z026" hand="#Wilde" place="inline above" rend="caret">or</add><milestone facs="#f018_z026" unit="caret"/>for pleasure, or <lb/>appeals strongly to our sympathies, or is</p>
				</sp>
			</div>
